          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-16 19:05:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nYes, that is the right order. I'm just confused by why some of the release jobs were succeeding. Only policy/common should succeed right now. I think it maybe was missing version.properties, so actually only SNAPSHOTS were actually being built.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "878584d66d90908d86863984e2a462da0e57d025",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2787,
          "name": "Liam Fallon",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
          "username": "liamfallon"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-16 19:54:31.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI handled this a different way here. I left the drools-applications dependency at 1.2.1-SNAPSHOT in this review. That allows engine 1.2.2-SNAPSHOT to build.\n\nOnce that builds then drools-applications can be built and released. Then we go back and do another review on the engine to fix the dependencies on drools applications. I explained what I was trying to do on a JIRA comment here:\nhttps://jira.onap.org/browse/POLICY-798",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
